150 grams Basmati Rice
240 grams British Beef Mince
1 sachet(s) Cajun Spice Mix
30 grams Tomato Puree
75 grams Creme Fraiche
10 grams Chicken Stock Paste
120 grams Peas
1 sachet(s) Crispy Onions
1 tbsp Honey
75 milliliter(s) Water

Boil a half-full kettle.
Pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the mince and Cajun spice mix (add less if you'd prefer things milder), 5-6 mins.
Break it up as it cooks, then drain the fat.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the tomato puree, creme fraiche, chicken stock, peas, honey, water (see pantry for both) and a knob of butter (if you have any). Stir to combine.
Bring to the boil and simmer, 2-3 mins.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the rice between bowls.
Top with the Cajun beef.
Sprinkle over the crispy onions.
Enjoy!